3729 static int mov_write_mfhd_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov)
3730 {
3731  avio_wb32(pb, 16);
3732  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "mfhd");
3733  avio_wb32(pb, 0);
3734  avio_wb32(pb, mov->fragments);
3735  return 0;
3736 }
3737 
3738 static uint32_t get_sample_flags(MOVTrack *track, MOVIentry *entry)
3739 {
3740  return entry->flags & MOV_SYNC_SAMPLE ? MOV_FRAG_SAMPLE_FLAG_DEPENDS_NO :
3741  (MOV_FRAG_SAMPLE_FLAG_DEPENDS_YES | MOV_FRAG_SAMPLE_FLAG_IS_NON_SYNC);
3742 }
3743 
3744 static int mov_write_tfhd_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov,
3745  MOVTrack *track, int64_t moof_offset)
3746 {
3747  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb);
3748  uint32_t flags = MOV_TFHD_DEFAULT_SIZE | MOV_TFHD_DEFAULT_DURATION |
3749  MOV_TFHD_BASE_DATA_OFFSET;
3750  if (!track->entry) {
3751  flags |= MOV_TFHD_DURATION_IS_EMPTY;
3752  } else {
3753  flags |= MOV_TFHD_DEFAULT_FLAGS;
3754  }
3755  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_OMIT_TFHD_OFFSET)
3756  flags &= ~MOV_TFHD_BASE_DATA_OFFSET;
3757  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DEFAULT_BASE_MOOF) {
3758  flags &= ~MOV_TFHD_BASE_DATA_OFFSET;
3759  flags |= MOV_TFHD_DEFAULT_BASE_IS_MOOF;
3760  }
3761 
3762  /* Don't set a default sample size, the silverlight player refuses
3763  * to play files with that set. Don't set a default sample duration,
3764  * WMP freaks out if it is set. Don't set a base data offset, PIFF
3765  * file format says it MUST NOT be set. */
3766  if (track->mode == MODE_ISM)
3767  flags &= ~(MOV_TFHD_DEFAULT_SIZE | MOV_TFHD_DEFAULT_DURATION |
3768  MOV_TFHD_BASE_DATA_OFFSET);
3769 
3770  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size placeholder */
3771  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "tfhd");
3772  avio_w8(pb, 0); /* version */
3773  avio_wb24(pb, flags);
3774 
3775  avio_wb32(pb, track->track_id); /* track-id */
3776  if (flags & MOV_TFHD_BASE_DATA_OFFSET)
3777  avio_wb64(pb, moof_offset);
3778  if (flags & MOV_TFHD_DEFAULT_DURATION) {
3779  track->default_duration = get_cluster_duration(track, 0);
3780  avio_wb32(pb, track->default_duration);
3781  }
3782  if (flags & MOV_TFHD_DEFAULT_SIZE) {
3783  track->default_size = track->entry ? track->cluster[0].size : 1;
3784  avio_wb32(pb, track->default_size);
3785  } else
3786  track->default_size = -1;
3787 
3788  if (flags & MOV_TFHD_DEFAULT_FLAGS) {
3789  /* Set the default flags based on the second sample, if available.
3790  * If the first sample is different, that can be signaled via a separate field. */
3791  if (track->entry > 1)
3792  track->default_sample_flags = get_sample_flags(track, &track->cluster[1]);
3793  else
3794  track->default_sample_flags =
3795  track->par->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ?
3796  (MOV_FRAG_SAMPLE_FLAG_DEPENDS_YES | MOV_FRAG_SAMPLE_FLAG_IS_NON_SYNC) :
3797  MOV_FRAG_SAMPLE_FLAG_DEPENDS_NO;
3798  avio_wb32(pb, track->default_sample_flags);
3799  }
3800 
3801  return update_size(pb, pos);
3802 }
3803 
3804 static int mov_write_trun_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov,
3805  MOVTrack *track, int moof_size,
3806  int first, int end)
3807 {
3808  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb);
3809  uint32_t flags = MOV_TRUN_DATA_OFFSET;
3810  int i;
3811 
3812  for (i = first; i < end; i++) {
3813  if (get_cluster_duration(track, i) != track->default_duration)
3814  flags |= MOV_TRUN_SAMPLE_DURATION;
3815  if (track->cluster[i].size != track->default_size)
3816  flags |= MOV_TRUN_SAMPLE_SIZE;
3817  if (i > first && get_sample_flags(track, &track->cluster[i]) != track->default_sample_flags)
3818  flags |= MOV_TRUN_SAMPLE_FLAGS;
3819  }
3820  if (!(flags & MOV_TRUN_SAMPLE_FLAGS) && track->entry > 0 &&
3821  get_sample_flags(track, &track->cluster[0]) != track->default_sample_flags)
3822  flags |= MOV_TRUN_FIRST_SAMPLE_FLAGS;
3823  if (track->flags & MOV_TRACK_CTTS)
3824  flags |= MOV_TRUN_SAMPLE_CTS;
3825 
3826  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size placeholder */
3827  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "trun");
3828  avio_w8(pb, 0); /* version */
3829  avio_wb24(pb, flags);
3830 
3831  avio_wb32(pb, end - first); /* sample count */
3832  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_OMIT_TFHD_OFFSET &&
3833  !(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DEFAULT_BASE_MOOF) &&
3834  !mov->first_trun)
3835  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* Later tracks follow immediately after the previous one */
3836  else
3837  avio_wb32(pb, moof_size + 8 + track->data_offset +
3838  track->cluster[first].pos); /* data offset */
3839  if (flags & MOV_TRUN_FIRST_SAMPLE_FLAGS)
3840  avio_wb32(pb, get_sample_flags(track, &track->cluster[first]));
3841 
3842  for (i = first; i < end; i++) {
3843  if (flags & MOV_TRUN_SAMPLE_DURATION)
3844  avio_wb32(pb, get_cluster_duration(track, i));
3845  if (flags & MOV_TRUN_SAMPLE_SIZE)
3846  avio_wb32(pb, track->cluster[i].size);
3847  if (flags & MOV_TRUN_SAMPLE_FLAGS)
3848  avio_wb32(pb, get_sample_flags(track, &track->cluster[i]));
3849  if (flags & MOV_TRUN_SAMPLE_CTS)
3850  avio_wb32(pb, track->cluster[i].cts);
3851  }
3852 
3853  mov->first_trun = 0;
3854  return update_size(pb, pos);
3855 }
3856 
3857 static int mov_write_tfxd_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVTrack *track)
3858 {
3859  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb);
3860  static const uint8_t uuid[] = {
3861  0x6d, 0x1d, 0x9b, 0x05, 0x42, 0xd5, 0x44, 0xe6,
3862  0x80, 0xe2, 0x14, 0x1d, 0xaf, 0xf7, 0x57, 0xb2
3863  };
3864 
3865  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size placeholder */
3866  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "uuid");
3867  avio_write(pb, uuid, sizeof(uuid));
3868  avio_w8(pb, 1);
3869  avio_wb24(pb, 0);
3870  avio_wb64(pb, track->start_dts + track->frag_start +
3871  track->cluster[0].cts);
3872  avio_wb64(pb, track->end_pts -
3873  (track->cluster[0].dts + track->cluster[0].cts));
3874 
3875  return update_size(pb, pos);
3876 }
3877 
3878 static int mov_write_tfrf_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov,
3879  MOVTrack *track, int entry)
3880 {
3881  int n = track->nb_frag_info - 1 - entry, i;
3882  int size = 8 + 16 + 4 + 1 + 16*n;
3883  static const uint8_t uuid[] = {
3884  0xd4, 0x80, 0x7e, 0xf2, 0xca, 0x39, 0x46, 0x95,
3885  0x8e, 0x54, 0x26, 0xcb, 0x9e, 0x46, 0xa7, 0x9f
3886  };
3887 
3888  if (entry < 0)
3889  return 0;
3890 
3891  avio_seek(pb, track->frag_info[entry].tfrf_offset, SEEK_SET);
3892  avio_wb32(pb, size);
3893  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "uuid");
3894  avio_write(pb, uuid, sizeof(uuid));
3895  avio_w8(pb, 1);
3896  avio_wb24(pb, 0);
3897  avio_w8(pb, n);
3898  for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
3899  int index = entry + 1 + i;
3900  avio_wb64(pb, track->frag_info[index].time);
3901  avio_wb64(pb, track->frag_info[index].duration);
3902  }
3903  if (n < mov->ism_lookahead) {
3904  int free_size = 16 * (mov->ism_lookahead - n);
3905  avio_wb32(pb, free_size);
3906  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "free");
3907  ffio_fill(pb, 0, free_size - 8);
3908  }
3909 
3910  return 0;
3911 }
3912 
3913 static int mov_write_tfrf_tags(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov,
3914  MOVTrack *track)
3915 {
3916  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb);
3917  int i;
3918  for (i = 0; i < mov->ism_lookahead; i++) {
3919  /* Update the tfrf tag for the last ism_lookahead fragments,
3920  * nb_frag_info - 1 is the next fragment to be written. */
3921  mov_write_tfrf_tag(pb, mov, track, track->nb_frag_info - 2 - i);
3922  }
3923  avio_seek(pb, pos, SEEK_SET);
3924  return 0;
3925 }
3926 
3927 static int mov_add_tfra_entries(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov, int tracks,
3928  int size)
3929 {
3930  int i;
3931  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
3932  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
3933  MOVFragmentInfo *info;
3934  if ((tracks >= 0 && i != tracks) || !track->entry)
3935  continue;
3936  track->nb_frag_info++;
3937  if (track->nb_frag_info >= track->frag_info_capacity) {
3938  unsigned new_capacity = track->nb_frag_info + MOV_FRAG_INFO_ALLOC_INCREMENT;
3939  if (av_reallocp_array(&track->frag_info,
3940  new_capacity,
3941  sizeof(*track->frag_info)))
3942  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
3943  track->frag_info_capacity = new_capacity;
3944  }
3945  info = &track->frag_info[track->nb_frag_info - 1];
3946  info->offset = avio_tell(pb);
3947  info->size = size;
3948  // Try to recreate the original pts for the first packet
3949  // from the fields we have stored
3950  info->time = track->start_dts + track->frag_start +
3951  track->cluster[0].cts;
3952  info->duration = track->end_pts -
3953  (track->cluster[0].dts + track->cluster[0].cts);
3954  // If the pts is less than zero, we will have trimmed
3955  // away parts of the media track using an edit list,
3956  // and the corresponding start presentation time is zero.
3957  if (info->time < 0) {
3958  info->duration += info->time;
3959  info->time = 0;
3960  }
3961  info->tfrf_offset = 0;
3962  mov_write_tfrf_tags(pb, mov, track);
3963  }
3964  return 0;
3965 }
3966 
3967 static void mov_prune_frag_info(MOVMuxContext *mov, int tracks, int max)
3968 {
3969  int i;
3970  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
3971  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
3972  if ((tracks >= 0 && i != tracks) || !track->entry)
3973  continue;
3974  if (track->nb_frag_info > max) {
3975  memmove(track->frag_info, track->frag_info + (track->nb_frag_info - max), max * sizeof(*track->frag_info));
3976  track->nb_frag_info = max;
3977  }
3978  }
3979 }
3980 
3981 static int mov_write_tfdt_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVTrack *track)
3982 {
3983  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb);
3984 
3985  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size */
3986  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "tfdt");
3987  avio_w8(pb, 1); /* version */
3988  avio_wb24(pb, 0);
3989  avio_wb64(pb, track->frag_start);
3990  return update_size(pb, pos);
3991 }
3992 
3993 static int mov_write_traf_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov,
3994  MOVTrack *track, int64_t moof_offset,
3995  int moof_size)
3996 {
3997  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb);
3998  int i, start = 0;
3999  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size placeholder */
4000  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "traf");
4001 
4002  mov_write_tfhd_tag(pb, mov, track, moof_offset);
4003  if (mov->mode != MODE_ISM)
4004  mov_write_tfdt_tag(pb, track);
4005  for (i = 1; i < track->entry; i++) {
4006  if (track->cluster[i].pos != track->cluster[i - 1].pos + track->cluster[i - 1].size) {
4007  mov_write_trun_tag(pb, mov, track, moof_size, start, i);
4008  start = i;
4009  }
4010  }
4011  mov_write_trun_tag(pb, mov, track, moof_size, start, track->entry);
4012  if (mov->mode == MODE_ISM) {
4013  mov_write_tfxd_tag(pb, track);
4014 
4015  if (mov->ism_lookahead) {
4016  int i, size = 16 + 4 + 1 + 16 * mov->ism_lookahead;
4017 
4018  if (track->nb_frag_info > 0) {
4019  MOVFragmentInfo *info = &track->frag_info[track->nb_frag_info - 1];
4020  if (!info->tfrf_offset)
4021  info->tfrf_offset = avio_tell(pb);
4022  }
4023  avio_wb32(pb, 8 + size);
4024  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "free");
4025  for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
4026  avio_w8(pb, 0);
4027  }
4028  }
4029 
4030  return update_size(pb, pos);
4031 }
4032 
4033 static int mov_write_moof_tag_internal(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov,
4034  int tracks, int moof_size)
4035 {
4036  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb);
4037  int i;
4038 
4039  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size placeholder */
4040  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "moof");
4041  mov->first_trun = 1;
4042 
4043  mov_write_mfhd_tag(pb, mov);
4044  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
4045  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
4046  if (tracks >= 0 && i != tracks)
4047  continue;
4048  if (!track->entry)
4049  continue;
4050  mov_write_traf_tag(pb, mov, track, pos, moof_size);
4051  }
4052 
4053  return update_size(pb, pos);
4054 }
4055 
4056 static int mov_write_sidx_tag(AVIOContext *pb,
4057  MOVTrack *track, int ref_size, int total_sidx_size)
4058 {
4059  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb), offset_pos, end_pos;
4060  int64_t presentation_time, duration, offset;
4061  int starts_with_SAP, i, entries;
4062 
4063  if (track->entry) {
4064  entries = 1;
4065  presentation_time = track->start_dts + track->frag_start +
4066  track->cluster[0].cts;
4067  duration = track->end_pts -
4068  (track->cluster[0].dts + track->cluster[0].cts);
4069  starts_with_SAP = track->cluster[0].flags & MOV_SYNC_SAMPLE;
4070 
4071  // pts<0 should be cut away using edts
4072  if (presentation_time < 0) {
4073  duration += presentation_time;
4074  presentation_time = 0;
4075  }
4076  } else {
4077  entries = track->nb_frag_info;
4078  if (entries <= 0)
4079  return 0;
4080  presentation_time = track->frag_info[0].time;
4081  }
4082 
4083  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size */
4084  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "sidx");
4085  avio_w8(pb, 1); /* version */
4086  avio_wb24(pb, 0);
4087  avio_wb32(pb, track->track_id); /* reference_ID */
4088  avio_wb32(pb, track->timescale); /* timescale */
4089  avio_wb64(pb, presentation_time); /* earliest_presentation_time */
4090  offset_pos = avio_tell(pb);
4091  avio_wb64(pb, 0); /* first_offset (offset to referenced moof) */
4092  avio_wb16(pb, 0); /* reserved */
4093 
4094  avio_wb16(pb, entries); /* reference_count */
4095  for (i = 0; i < entries; i++) {
4096  if (!track->entry) {
4097  if (i > 1 && track->frag_info[i].offset != track->frag_info[i - 1].offset + track->frag_info[i - 1].size) {
4098  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Non-consecutive fragments, writing incorrect sidx\n");
4099  }
4100  duration = track->frag_info[i].duration;
4101  ref_size = track->frag_info[i].size;
4102  starts_with_SAP = 1;
4103  }
4104  avio_wb32(pb, (0 << 31) | (ref_size & 0x7fffffff)); /* reference_type (0 = media) | referenced_size */
4105  avio_wb32(pb, duration); /* subsegment_duration */
4106  avio_wb32(pb, (starts_with_SAP << 31) | (0 << 28) | 0); /* starts_with_SAP | SAP_type | SAP_delta_time */
4107  }
4108 
4109  end_pos = avio_tell(pb);
4110  offset = pos + total_sidx_size - end_pos;
4111  avio_seek(pb, offset_pos, SEEK_SET);
4112  avio_wb64(pb, offset);
4113  avio_seek(pb, end_pos, SEEK_SET);
4114  return update_size(pb, pos);
4115 }
4116 
4117 static int mov_write_sidx_tags(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov,
4118  int tracks, int ref_size)
4119 {
4120  int i, round, ret;
4121  AVIOContext *avio_buf;
4122  int total_size = 0;
4123  for (round = 0; round < 2; round++) {
4124  // First run one round to calculate the total size of all
4125  // sidx atoms.
4126  // This would be much simpler if we'd only write one sidx
4127  // atom, for the first track in the moof.
4128  if (round == 0) {
4129  if ((ret = ffio_open_null_buf(&avio_buf)) < 0)
4130  return ret;
4131  } else {
4132  avio_buf = pb;
4133  }
4134  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
4135  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
4136  if (tracks >= 0 && i != tracks)
4137  continue;
4138  // When writing a sidx for the full file, entry is 0, but
4139  // we want to include all tracks. ref_size is 0 in this case,
4140  // since we read it from frag_info instead.
4141  if (!track->entry && ref_size > 0)
4142  continue;
4143  total_size -= mov_write_sidx_tag(avio_buf, track, ref_size,
4144  total_size);
4145  }
4146  if (round == 0)
4147  total_size = ffio_close_null_buf(avio_buf);
4148  }
4149  return 0;
4150 }
4151 
4152 static int mov_write_moof_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov, int tracks,
4153  int64_t mdat_size)
4154 {
4155  AVIOContext *avio_buf;
4156  int ret, moof_size;
4157 
4158  if ((ret = ffio_open_null_buf(&avio_buf)) < 0)
4159  return ret;
4160  mov_write_moof_tag_internal(avio_buf, mov, tracks, 0);
4161  moof_size = ffio_close_null_buf(avio_buf);
4162 
4163  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DASH && !(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_GLOBAL_SIDX))
4164  mov_write_sidx_tags(pb, mov, tracks, moof_size + 8 + mdat_size);
4165 
4166  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_GLOBAL_SIDX ||
4167  !(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_SKIP_TRAILER) ||
4168  mov->ism_lookahead) {
4169  if ((ret = mov_add_tfra_entries(pb, mov, tracks, moof_size + 8 + mdat_size)) < 0)
4170  return ret;
4171  if (!(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_GLOBAL_SIDX) &&
4172  mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_SKIP_TRAILER) {
4173  mov_prune_frag_info(mov, tracks, mov->ism_lookahead + 1);
4174  }
4175  }
4176 
4177  return mov_write_moof_tag_internal(pb, mov, tracks, moof_size);
4178 }
4179 
4180 static int mov_write_tfra_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVTrack *track)
4181 {
4182  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb);
4183  int i;
4184 
4185  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size placeholder */
4186  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "tfra");
4187  avio_w8(pb, 1); /* version */
4188  avio_wb24(pb, 0);
4189 
4190  avio_wb32(pb, track->track_id);
4191  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* length of traf/trun/sample num */
4192  avio_wb32(pb, track->nb_frag_info);
4193  for (i = 0; i < track->nb_frag_info; i++) {
4194  avio_wb64(pb, track->frag_info[i].time);
4195  avio_wb64(pb, track->frag_info[i].offset + track->data_offset);
4196  avio_w8(pb, 1); /* traf number */
4197  avio_w8(pb, 1); /* trun number */
4198  avio_w8(pb, 1); /* sample number */
4199  }
4200 
4201  return update_size(pb, pos);
4202 }
4203 
4204 static int mov_write_mfra_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov)
4205 {
4206  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb);
4207  int i;
4208 
4209  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size placeholder */
4210  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "mfra");
4211  /* An empty mfra atom is enough to indicate to the publishing point that
4212  * the stream has ended. */
4213  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_ISML)
4214  return update_size(pb, pos);
4215 
4216  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
4217  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
4218  if (track->nb_frag_info)
4219  mov_write_tfra_tag(pb, track);
4220  }
4221 
4222  avio_wb32(pb, 16);
4223  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "mfro");
4224  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* version + flags */
4225  avio_wb32(pb, avio_tell(pb) + 4 - pos);
4226 
4227  return update_size(pb, pos);
4228 }
4229 
4230 static int mov_write_mdat_tag(AVIOContext *pb, MOVMuxContext *mov)
4231 {
4232  avio_wb32(pb, 8); // placeholder for extended size field (64 bit)
4233  ffio_wfourcc(pb, mov->mode == MODE_MOV ? "wide" : "free");
4234 
4235  mov->mdat_pos = avio_tell(pb);
4236  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size placeholder*/
4237  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "mdat");
4238  return 0;
4239 }
4240 
4241 /* TODO: This needs to be more general */
4242 static int mov_write_ftyp_tag(AVIOContext *pb, AVFormatContext *s)
4243 {
4244  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
4245  int64_t pos = avio_tell(pb);
4246  int has_h264 = 0, has_video = 0;
4247  int minor = 0x200;
4248  int i;
4249 
4250  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
4251  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
4252  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
4253  has_video = 1;
4254  if (st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264)
4255  has_h264 = 1;
4256  }
4257 
4258  avio_wb32(pb, 0); /* size */
4259  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "ftyp");
4260 
4261  if (mov->major_brand && strlen(mov->major_brand) >= 4)
4262  ffio_wfourcc(pb, mov->major_brand);
4263  else if (mov->mode == MODE_3GP) {
4264  ffio_wfourcc(pb, has_h264 ? "3gp6" : "3gp4");
4265  minor = has_h264 ? 0x100 : 0x200;
4266  } else if (mov->mode & MODE_3G2) {
4267  ffio_wfourcc(pb, has_h264 ? "3g2b" : "3g2a");
4268  minor = has_h264 ? 0x20000 : 0x10000;
4269  } else if (mov->mode == MODE_PSP)
4270  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "MSNV");
4271  else if (mov->mode == MODE_MP4 && mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DEFAULT_BASE_MOOF)
4272  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "iso5"); // Required when using default-base-is-moof
4273  else if (mov->mode == MODE_MP4)
4274  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "isom");
4275  else if (mov->mode == MODE_IPOD)
4276  ffio_wfourcc(pb, has_video ? "M4V ":"M4A ");
4277  else if (mov->mode == MODE_ISM)
4278  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "isml");
4279  else if (mov->mode == MODE_F4V)
4280  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "f4v ");
4281  else
4282  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "qt ");
4283 
4284  avio_wb32(pb, minor);
4285 
4286  if (mov->mode == MODE_MOV)
4287  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "qt ");
4288  else if (mov->mode == MODE_ISM) {
4289  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "piff");
4290  } else if (!(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DEFAULT_BASE_MOOF)) {
4291  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "isom");
4292  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "iso2");
4293  if (has_h264)
4294  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "avc1");
4295  }
4296 
4297  // We add tfdt atoms when fragmenting, signal this with the iso6 compatible
4298  // brand. This is compatible with users that don't understand tfdt.
4299  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT && mov->mode != MODE_ISM)
4300  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "iso6");
4301 
4302  if (mov->mode == MODE_3GP)
4303  ffio_wfourcc(pb, has_h264 ? "3gp6":"3gp4");
4304  else if (mov->mode & MODE_3G2)
4305  ffio_wfourcc(pb, has_h264 ? "3g2b":"3g2a");
4306  else if (mov->mode == MODE_PSP)
4307  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "MSNV");
4308  else if (mov->mode == MODE_MP4)
4309  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "mp41");
4310 
4311  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DASH && mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_GLOBAL_SIDX)
4312  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "dash");
4313 
4314  return update_size(pb, pos);
4315 }
4316 
4317 static int mov_write_uuidprof_tag(AVIOContext *pb, AVFormatContext *s)
4318 {
4319  AVStream *video_st = s->streams[0];
4320  AVCodecParameters *video_par = s->streams[0]->codecpar;
4321  AVCodecParameters *audio_par = s->streams[1]->codecpar;
4322  int audio_rate = audio_par->sample_rate;
4323  int64_t frame_rate = video_st->avg_frame_rate.den ?
4324  (video_st->avg_frame_rate.num * 0x10000LL) / video_st->avg_frame_rate.den :
4325  0;
4326  int audio_kbitrate = audio_par->bit_rate / 1000;
4327  int video_kbitrate = FFMIN(video_par->bit_rate / 1000, 800 - audio_kbitrate);
4328 
4329  if (frame_rate < 0 || frame_rate > INT32_MAX) {
4330  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Frame rate %f outside supported range\n", frame_rate / (double)0x10000);
4331  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
4332  }
4333 
4334  avio_wb32(pb, 0x94); /* size */
4335  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "uuid");
4336  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "PROF");
4337 
4338  avio_wb32(pb, 0x21d24fce); /* 96 bit UUID */
4339  avio_wb32(pb, 0xbb88695c);
4340  avio_wb32(pb, 0xfac9c740);
4341 
4342  avio_wb32(pb, 0x0); /* ? */
4343  avio_wb32(pb, 0x3); /* 3 sections ? */
4344 
4345  avio_wb32(pb, 0x14); /* size */
4346  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "FPRF");
4347  avio_wb32(pb, 0x0); /* ? */
4348  avio_wb32(pb, 0x0); /* ? */
4349  avio_wb32(pb, 0x0); /* ? */
4350 
4351  avio_wb32(pb, 0x2c); /* size */
4352  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "APRF"); /* audio */
4353  avio_wb32(pb, 0x0);
4354  avio_wb32(pb, 0x2); /* TrackID */
4355  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "mp4a");
4356  avio_wb32(pb, 0x20f);
4357  avio_wb32(pb, 0x0);
4358  avio_wb32(pb, audio_kbitrate);
4359  avio_wb32(pb, audio_kbitrate);
4360  avio_wb32(pb, audio_rate);
4361  avio_wb32(pb, audio_par->channels);
4362 
4363  avio_wb32(pb, 0x34); /* size */
4364  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "VPRF"); /* video */
4365  avio_wb32(pb, 0x0);
4366  avio_wb32(pb, 0x1); /* TrackID */
4367  if (video_par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264) {
4368  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "avc1");
4369  avio_wb16(pb, 0x014D);
4370  avio_wb16(pb, 0x0015);
4371  } else {
4372  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "mp4v");
4373  avio_wb16(pb, 0x0000);
4374  avio_wb16(pb, 0x0103);
4375  }
4376  avio_wb32(pb, 0x0);
4377  avio_wb32(pb, video_kbitrate);
4378  avio_wb32(pb, video_kbitrate);
4379  avio_wb32(pb, frame_rate);
4380  avio_wb32(pb, frame_rate);
4381  avio_wb16(pb, video_par->width);
4382  avio_wb16(pb, video_par->height);
4383  avio_wb32(pb, 0x010001); /* ? */
4384 
4385  return 0;
4386 }
4387 
4388 static int mov_write_identification(AVIOContext *pb, AVFormatContext *s)
4389 {
4390  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
4391  int i;
4392 
4393  mov_write_ftyp_tag(pb,s);
4394  if (mov->mode == MODE_PSP) {
4395  int video_streams_nb = 0, audio_streams_nb = 0, other_streams_nb = 0;
4396  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
4397  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
4398  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
4399  video_streams_nb++;
4400  else if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO)
4401  audio_streams_nb++;
4402  else
4403  other_streams_nb++;
4404  }
4405 
4406  if (video_streams_nb != 1 || audio_streams_nb != 1 || other_streams_nb) {
4407  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "PSP mode need one video and one audio stream\n");
4408  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
4409  }
4410  return mov_write_uuidprof_tag(pb, s);
4411  }
4412  return 0;
4413 }
4414 
4415 static int mov_parse_mpeg2_frame(AVPacket *pkt, uint32_t *flags)
4416 {
4417  uint32_t c = -1;
4418  int i, closed_gop = 0;
4419 
4420  for (i = 0; i < pkt->size - 4; i++) {
4421  c = (c << 8) + pkt->data[i];
4422  if (c == 0x1b8) { // gop
4423  closed_gop = pkt->data[i + 4] >> 6 & 0x01;
4424  } else if (c == 0x100) { // pic
4425  int temp_ref = (pkt->data[i + 1] << 2) | (pkt->data[i + 2] >> 6);
4426  if (!temp_ref || closed_gop) // I picture is not reordered
4427  *flags = MOV_SYNC_SAMPLE;
4428  else
4429  *flags = MOV_PARTIAL_SYNC_SAMPLE;
4430  break;
4431  }
4432  }
4433  return 0;
4434 }
4435 
4436 static void mov_parse_vc1_frame(AVPacket *pkt, MOVTrack *trk)
4437 {
4438  const uint8_t *start, *next, *end = pkt->data + pkt->size;
4439  int seq = 0, entry = 0;
4440  int key = pkt->flags & AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY;
4441  start = find_next_marker(pkt->data, end);
4442  for (next = start; next < end; start = next) {
4443  next = find_next_marker(start + 4, end);
4444  switch (AV_RB32(start)) {
4445  case VC1_CODE_SEQHDR:
4446  seq = 1;
4447  break;
4448  case VC1_CODE_ENTRYPOINT:
4449  entry = 1;
4450  break;
4451  case VC1_CODE_SLICE:
4452  trk->vc1_info.slices = 1;
4453  break;
4454  }
4455  }
4456  if (!trk->entry && trk->vc1_info.first_packet_seen)
4457  trk->vc1_info.first_frag_written = 1;
4458  if (!trk->entry && !trk->vc1_info.first_frag_written) {
4459  /* First packet in first fragment */
4460  trk->vc1_info.first_packet_seq = seq;
4461  trk->vc1_info.first_packet_entry = entry;
4462  trk->vc1_info.first_packet_seen = 1;
4463  } else if ((seq && !trk->vc1_info.packet_seq) ||
4464  (entry && !trk->vc1_info.packet_entry)) {
4465  int i;
4466  for (i = 0; i < trk->entry; i++)
4467  trk->cluster[i].flags &= ~MOV_SYNC_SAMPLE;
4468  trk->has_keyframes = 0;
4469  if (seq)
4470  trk->vc1_info.packet_seq = 1;
4471  if (entry)
4472  trk->vc1_info.packet_entry = 1;
4473  if (!trk->vc1_info.first_frag_written) {
4474  /* First fragment */
4475  if ((!seq || trk->vc1_info.first_packet_seq) &&
4476  (!entry || trk->vc1_info.first_packet_entry)) {
4477  /* First packet had the same headers as this one, readd the
4478  * sync sample flag. */
4479  trk->cluster[0].flags |= MOV_SYNC_SAMPLE;
4480  trk->has_keyframes = 1;
4481  }
4482  }
4483  }
4484  if (trk->vc1_info.packet_seq && trk->vc1_info.packet_entry)
4485  key = seq && entry;
4486  else if (trk->vc1_info.packet_seq)
4487  key = seq;
4488  else if (trk->vc1_info.packet_entry)
4489  key = entry;
4490  if (key) {
4491  trk->cluster[trk->entry].flags |= MOV_SYNC_SAMPLE;
4492  trk->has_keyframes++;
4493  }
4494 }
4495 
4496 static int mov_flush_fragment_interleaving(AVFormatContext *s, MOVTrack *track)
4497 {
4498  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
4499  int ret, buf_size;
4500  uint8_t *buf;
4501  int i, offset;
4502 
4503  if (!track->mdat_buf)
4504  return 0;
4505  if (!mov->mdat_buf) {
4506  if ((ret = avio_open_dyn_buf(&mov->mdat_buf)) < 0)
4507  return ret;
4508  }
4509  buf_size = avio_close_dyn_buf(track->mdat_buf, &buf);
4510  track->mdat_buf = NULL;
4511 
4512  offset = avio_tell(mov->mdat_buf);
4513  avio_write(mov->mdat_buf, buf, buf_size);
4514  av_free(buf);
4515 
4516  for (i = track->entries_flushed; i < track->entry; i++)
4517  track->cluster[i].pos += offset;
4518  track->entries_flushed = track->entry;
4519  return 0;
4520 }
4521 
4522 static int mov_flush_fragment(AVFormatContext *s, int force)
4523 {
4524  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
4525  int i, first_track = -1;
4526  int64_t mdat_size = 0;
4527  int ret;
4528  int has_video = 0, starts_with_key = 0, first_video_track = 1;
4529 
4530  if (!(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT))
4531  return 0;
4532 
4533  // Try to fill in the duration of the last packet in each stream
4534  // from queued packets in the interleave queues. If the flushing
4535  // of fragments was triggered automatically by an AVPacket, we
4536  // already have reliable info for the end of that track, but other
4537  // tracks may need to be filled in.
4538  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
4539  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
4540  if (!track->end_reliable) {
4541  AVPacket pkt;
4542  if (!ff_interleaved_peek(s, i, &pkt, 1)) {
4543  track->track_duration = pkt.dts - track->start_dts;
4544  if (pkt.pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
4545  track->end_pts = pkt.pts;
4546  else
4547  track->end_pts = pkt.dts;
4548  }
4549  }
4550  }
4551 
4552  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
4553  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
4554  if (track->entry <= 1)
4555  continue;
4556  // Sample durations are calculated as the diff of dts values,
4557  // but for the last sample in a fragment, we don't know the dts
4558  // of the first sample in the next fragment, so we have to rely
4559  // on what was set as duration in the AVPacket. Not all callers
4560  // set this though, so we might want to replace it with an
4561  // estimate if it currently is zero.
4562  if (get_cluster_duration(track, track->entry - 1) != 0)
4563  continue;
4564  // Use the duration (i.e. dts diff) of the second last sample for
4565  // the last one. This is a wild guess (and fatal if it turns out
4566  // to be too long), but probably the best we can do - having a zero
4567  // duration is bad as well.
4568  track->track_duration += get_cluster_duration(track, track->entry - 2);
4569  track->end_pts += get_cluster_duration(track, track->entry - 2);
4570  if (!mov->missing_duration_warned) {
4571  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING,
4572  "Estimating the duration of the last packet in a "
4573  "fragment, consider setting the duration field in "
4574  "AVPacket instead.\n");
4575  mov->missing_duration_warned = 1;
4576  }
4577  }
4578 
4579  if (!mov->moov_written) {
4580  int64_t pos = avio_tell(s->pb);
4581  uint8_t *buf;
4582  int buf_size, moov_size;
4583 
4584  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++)
4585  if (!mov->tracks[i].entry)
4586  break;
4587  /* Don't write the initial moov unless all tracks have data */
4588  if (i < mov->nb_streams && !force)
4589  return 0;
4590 
4591  moov_size = get_moov_size(s);
4592  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++)
4593  mov->tracks[i].data_offset = pos + moov_size + 8;
4594 
4595  avio_write_marker(s->pb, AV_NOPTS_VALUE, AVIO_DATA_MARKER_HEADER);
4596  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DELAY_MOOV)
4597  mov_write_identification(s->pb, s);
4598  if ((ret = mov_write_moov_tag(s->pb, mov, s)) < 0)
4599  return ret;
4600 
4601  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DELAY_MOOV) {
4602  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_GLOBAL_SIDX)
4603  mov->reserved_header_pos = avio_tell(s->pb);
4604  avio_flush(s->pb);
4605  mov->moov_written = 1;
4606  return 0;
4607  }
4608 
4609  buf_size = avio_close_dyn_buf(mov->mdat_buf, &buf);
4610  mov->mdat_buf = NULL;
4611  avio_wb32(s->pb, buf_size + 8);
4612  ffio_wfourcc(s->pb, "mdat");
4613  avio_write(s->pb, buf, buf_size);
4614  av_free(buf);
4615 
4616  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_GLOBAL_SIDX)
4617  mov->reserved_header_pos = avio_tell(s->pb);
4618 
4619  mov->moov_written = 1;
4620  mov->mdat_size = 0;
4621  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
4622  if (mov->tracks[i].entry)
4623  mov->tracks[i].frag_start += mov->tracks[i].start_dts +
4624  mov->tracks[i].track_duration -
4625  mov->tracks[i].cluster[0].dts;
4626  mov->tracks[i].entry = 0;
4627  mov->tracks[i].end_reliable = 0;
4628  }
4629  avio_flush(s->pb);
4630  return 0;
4631  }
4632 
4633  if (mov->frag_interleave) {
4634  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
4635  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
4636  int ret;
4637  if ((ret = mov_flush_fragment_interleaving(s, track)) < 0)
4638  return ret;
4639  }
4640 
4641  if (!mov->mdat_buf)
4642  return 0;
4643  mdat_size = avio_tell(mov->mdat_buf);
4644  }
4645 
4646  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
4647  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
4648  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_SEPARATE_MOOF || mov->frag_interleave)
4649  track->data_offset = 0;
4650  else
4651  track->data_offset = mdat_size;
4652  if (track->par->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
4653  has_video = 1;
4654  if (first_video_track) {
4655  if (track->entry)
4656  starts_with_key = track->cluster[0].flags & MOV_SYNC_SAMPLE;
4657  first_video_track = 0;
4658  }
4659  }
4660  if (!track->entry)
4661  continue;
4662  if (track->mdat_buf)
4663  mdat_size += avio_tell(track->mdat_buf);
4664  if (first_track < 0)
4665  first_track = i;
4666  }
4667 
4668  if (!mdat_size)
4669  return 0;
4670 
4671  avio_write_marker(s->pb,
4672  av_rescale(mov->tracks[first_track].cluster[0].dts, AV_TIME_BASE, mov->tracks[first_track].timescale),
4673  (has_video ? starts_with_key : mov->tracks[first_track].cluster[0].flags & MOV_SYNC_SAMPLE) ? AVIO_DATA_MARKER_SYNC_POINT : AVIO_DATA_MARKER_BOUNDARY_POINT);
4674 
4675  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
4676  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
4677  int buf_size, write_moof = 1, moof_tracks = -1;
4678  uint8_t *buf;
4679  int64_t duration = 0;
4680 
4681  if (track->entry)
4682  duration = track->start_dts + track->track_duration -
4683  track->cluster[0].dts;
4684  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_SEPARATE_MOOF) {
4685  if (!track->mdat_buf)
4686  continue;
4687  mdat_size = avio_tell(track->mdat_buf);
4688  moof_tracks = i;
4689  } else {
4690  write_moof = i == first_track;
4691  }
4692 
4693  if (write_moof) {
4694  avio_flush(s->pb);
4695 
4696  mov_write_moof_tag(s->pb, mov, moof_tracks, mdat_size);
4697  mov->fragments++;
4698 
4699  avio_wb32(s->pb, mdat_size + 8);
4700  ffio_wfourcc(s->pb, "mdat");
4701  }
4702 
4703  if (track->entry)
4704  track->frag_start += duration;
4705  track->entry = 0;
4706  track->entries_flushed = 0;
4707  track->end_reliable = 0;
4708  if (!mov->frag_interleave) {
4709  if (!track->mdat_buf)
4710  continue;
4711  buf_size = avio_close_dyn_buf(track->mdat_buf, &buf);
4712  track->mdat_buf = NULL;
4713  } else {
4714  if (!mov->mdat_buf)
4715  continue;
4716  buf_size = avio_close_dyn_buf(mov->mdat_buf, &buf);
4717  mov->mdat_buf = NULL;
4718  }
4719 
4720  avio_write(s->pb, buf, buf_size);
4721  av_free(buf);
4722  }
4723 
4724  mov->mdat_size = 0;
4725 
4726  avio_flush(s->pb);
4727  return 0;
4728 }
4729 
4730 static int mov_auto_flush_fragment(AVFormatContext *s, int force)
4731 {
4732  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
4733  int had_moov = mov->moov_written;
4734  int ret = mov_flush_fragment(s, force);
4735  if (ret < 0)
4736  return ret;
4737  // If using delay_moov, the first flush only wrote the moov,
4738  // not the actual moof+mdat pair, thus flush once again.
4739  if (!had_moov && mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DELAY_MOOV)
4740  ret = mov_flush_fragment(s, force);
4741  return ret;
4742 }
4743 
4744 static int check_pkt(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt)
4745 {
4746  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
4747  MOVTrack *trk = &mov->tracks[pkt->stream_index];
4748  int64_t ref;
4749  uint64_t duration;
4750 
4751  if (trk->entry) {
4752  ref = trk->cluster[trk->entry - 1].dts;
4753  } else if ( trk->start_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE
4754  && !trk->frag_discont) {
4755  ref = trk->start_dts + trk->track_duration;
4756  } else
4757  ref = pkt->dts; // Skip tests for the first packet
4758 
4759  duration = pkt->dts - ref;
4760  if (pkt->dts < ref || duration >= INT_MAX) {
4761  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Application provided duration: %"PRId64" / timestamp: %"PRId64" is out of range for mov/mp4 format\n",
4762  duration, pkt->dts
4763  );
4764 
4765  pkt->dts = ref + 1;
4766  pkt->pts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4767  }
4768 
4769  if (pkt->duration < 0 || pkt->duration > INT_MAX) {
4770  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Application provided duration: %"PRId64" is invalid\n", pkt->duration);
4771  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
4772  }
4773  return 0;
4774 }
4775 
4776 int ff_mov_write_packet(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt)
4777 {
4778  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
4779  AVIOContext *pb = s->pb;
4780  MOVTrack *trk = &mov->tracks[pkt->stream_index];
4781  AVCodecParameters *par = trk->par;
4782  unsigned int samples_in_chunk = 0;
4783  int size = pkt->size, ret = 0;
4784  uint8_t *reformatted_data = NULL;
4785 
4786  ret = check_pkt(s, pkt);
4787  if (ret < 0)
4788  return ret;
4789 
4790  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT) {
4791  int ret;
4792  if (mov->moov_written || mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_EMPTY_MOOV) {
4793  if (mov->frag_interleave && mov->fragments > 0) {
4794  if (trk->entry - trk->entries_flushed >= mov->frag_interleave) {
4795  if ((ret = mov_flush_fragment_interleaving(s, trk)) < 0)
4796  return ret;
4797  }
4798  }
4799 
4800  if (!trk->mdat_buf) {
4801  if ((ret = avio_open_dyn_buf(&trk->mdat_buf)) < 0)
4802  return ret;
4803  }
4804  pb = trk->mdat_buf;
4805  } else {
4806  if (!mov->mdat_buf) {
4807  if ((ret = avio_open_dyn_buf(&mov->mdat_buf)) < 0)
4808  return ret;
4809  }
4810  pb = mov->mdat_buf;
4811  }
4812  }
4813 
4814  if (par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_AMR_NB) {
4815  /* We must find out how many AMR blocks there are in one packet */
4816  static const uint16_t packed_size[16] =
4817  {13, 14, 16, 18, 20, 21, 27, 32, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1};
4818  int len = 0;
4819 
4820  while (len < size && samples_in_chunk < 100) {
4821  len += packed_size[(pkt->data[len] >> 3) & 0x0F];
4822  samples_in_chunk++;
4823  }
4824  if (samples_in_chunk > 1) {
4825  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "fatal error, input is not a single packet, implement a AVParser for it\n");
4826  return -1;
4827  }
4828  } else if (par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_ADPCM_MS ||
4829  par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_ADPCM_IMA_WAV) {
4830  samples_in_chunk = trk->par->frame_size;
4831  } else if (trk->sample_size)
4832  samples_in_chunk = size / trk->sample_size;
4833  else
4834  samples_in_chunk = 1;
4835 
4836  /* copy extradata if it exists */
4837  if (trk->vos_len == 0 && par->extradata_size > 0 &&
4838  !TAG_IS_AVCI(trk->tag) &&
4839  (par->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_DNXHD)) {
4840  trk->vos_len = par->extradata_size;
4841  trk->vos_data = av_malloc(trk->vos_len);
4842  if (!trk->vos_data) {
4843  ret = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4844  goto err;
4845  }
4846  memcpy(trk->vos_data, par->extradata, trk->vos_len);
4847  }
4848 
4849  if (par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_AAC && pkt->size > 2 &&
4850  (AV_RB16(pkt->data) & 0xfff0) == 0xfff0) {
4851  if (!s->streams[pkt->stream_index]->nb_frames) {
4852  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Malformed AAC bitstream detected: "
4853  "use the audio bitstream filter 'aac_adtstoasc' to fix it "
4854  "('-bsf:a aac_adtstoasc' option with ffmpeg)\n");
4855  return -1;
4856  }
4857  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING, "aac bitstream error\n");
4858  }
4859  if (par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264 && trk->vos_len > 0 && *(uint8_t *)trk->vos_data != 1 && !TAG_IS_AVCI(trk->tag)) {
4860  /* from x264 or from bytestream H.264 */
4861  /* NAL reformatting needed */
4862  if (trk->hint_track >= 0 && trk->hint_track < mov->nb_streams) {
4863  ff_avc_parse_nal_units_buf(pkt->data, &reformatted_data,
4864  &size);
4865  avio_write(pb, reformatted_data, size);
4866  } else {
4867  if (mov->encryption_scheme == MOV_ENC_CENC_AES_CTR) {
4868  size = ff_mov_cenc_avc_parse_nal_units(&trk->cenc, pb, pkt->data, size);
4869  if (size < 0) {
4870  ret = size;
4871  goto err;
4872  }
4873  } else {
4874  size = ff_avc_parse_nal_units(pb, pkt->data, pkt->size);
4875  }
4876  }
4877  } else if (par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_HEVC && trk->vos_len > 6 &&
4878  (AV_RB24(trk->vos_data) == 1 || AV_RB32(trk->vos_data) == 1)) {
4879  /* extradata is Annex B, assume the bitstream is too and convert it */
4880  if (trk->hint_track >= 0 && trk->hint_track < mov->nb_streams) {
4881  ff_hevc_annexb2mp4_buf(pkt->data, &reformatted_data, &size, 0, NULL);
4882  avio_write(pb, reformatted_data, size);
4883  } else {
4884  size = ff_hevc_annexb2mp4(pb, pkt->data, pkt->size, 0, NULL);
4885  }
4886 #if CONFIG_AC3_PARSER
4887  } else if (par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_EAC3) {
4888  size = handle_eac3(mov, pkt, trk);
4889  if (size < 0)
4890  return size;
4891  else if (!size)
4892  goto end;
4893  avio_write(pb, pkt->data, size);
4894 #endif
4895  } else {
4896  if (mov->encryption_scheme == MOV_ENC_CENC_AES_CTR) {
4897  if (par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264 && par->extradata_size > 4) {
4898  int nal_size_length = (par->extradata[4] & 0x3) + 1;
4899  ret = ff_mov_cenc_avc_write_nal_units(s, &trk->cenc, nal_size_length, pb, pkt->data, size);
4900  } else {
4901  ret = ff_mov_cenc_write_packet(&trk->cenc, pb, pkt->data, size);
4902  }
4903 
4904  if (ret) {
4905  goto err;
4906  }
4907  } else {
4908  avio_write(pb, pkt->data, size);
4909  }
4910  }
4911 
4912  if ((par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_DNXHD ||
4913  par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_AC3) && !trk->vos_len) {
4914  /* copy frame to create needed atoms */
4915  trk->vos_len = size;
4916  trk->vos_data = av_malloc(size);
4917  if (!trk->vos_data) {
4918  ret = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4919  goto err;
4920  }
4921  memcpy(trk->vos_data, pkt->data, size);
4922  }
4923 
4924  if (trk->entry >= trk->cluster_capacity) {
4925  unsigned new_capacity = 2 * (trk->entry + MOV_INDEX_CLUSTER_SIZE);
4926  if (av_reallocp_array(&trk->cluster, new_capacity,
4927  sizeof(*trk->cluster))) {
4928  ret = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4929  goto err;
4930  }
4931  trk->cluster_capacity = new_capacity;
4932  }
4933 
4934  trk->cluster[trk->entry].pos = avio_tell(pb) - size;
4935  trk->cluster[trk->entry].samples_in_chunk = samples_in_chunk;
4936  trk->cluster[trk->entry].chunkNum = 0;
4937  trk->cluster[trk->entry].size = size;
4938  trk->cluster[trk->entry].entries = samples_in_chunk;
4939  trk->cluster[trk->entry].dts = pkt->dts;
4940  if (!trk->entry && trk->start_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
4941  if (!trk->frag_discont) {
4942  /* First packet of a new fragment. We already wrote the duration
4943  * of the last packet of the previous fragment based on track_duration,
4944  * which might not exactly match our dts. Therefore adjust the dts
4945  * of this packet to be what the previous packets duration implies. */
4946  trk->cluster[trk->entry].dts = trk->start_dts + trk->track_duration;
4947  /* We also may have written the pts and the corresponding duration
4948  * in sidx/tfrf/tfxd tags; make sure the sidx pts and duration match up with
4949  * the next fragment. This means the cts of the first sample must
4950  * be the same in all fragments, unless end_pts was updated by
4951  * the packet causing the fragment to be written. */
4952  if ((mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DASH && !(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_GLOBAL_SIDX)) ||
4953  mov->mode == MODE_ISM)
4954  pkt->pts = pkt->dts + trk->end_pts - trk->cluster[trk->entry].dts;
4955  } else {
4956  /* New fragment, but discontinuous from previous fragments.
4957  * Pretend the duration sum of the earlier fragments is
4958  * pkt->dts - trk->start_dts. */
4959  trk->frag_start = pkt->dts - trk->start_dts;
4960  trk->end_pts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4961  trk->frag_discont = 0;
4962  }
4963  }
4964 
4965  if (!trk->entry && trk->start_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE && !mov->use_editlist &&
4966  s->avoid_negative_ts == AVFMT_AVOID_NEG_TS_MAKE_ZERO) {
4967  /* Not using edit lists and shifting the first track to start from zero.
4968  * If the other streams start from a later timestamp, we won't be able
4969  * to signal the difference in starting time without an edit list.
4970  * Thus move the timestamp for this first sample to 0, increasing
4971  * its duration instead. */
4972  trk->cluster[trk->entry].dts = trk->start_dts = 0;
4973  }
4974  if (trk->start_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
4975  trk->start_dts = pkt->dts;
4976  if (trk->frag_discont) {
4977  if (mov->use_editlist) {
4978  /* Pretend the whole stream started at pts=0, with earlier fragments
4979  * already written. If the stream started at pts=0, the duration sum
4980  * of earlier fragments would have been pkt->pts. */
4981  trk->frag_start = pkt->pts;
4982  trk->start_dts = pkt->dts - pkt->pts;
4983  } else {
4984  /* Pretend the whole stream started at dts=0, with earlier fragments
4985  * already written, with a duration summing up to pkt->dts. */
4986  trk->frag_start = pkt->dts;
4987  trk->start_dts = 0;
4988  }
4989  trk->frag_discont = 0;
4990  } else if (pkt->dts && mov->moov_written)
4991  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING,
4992  "Track %d starts with a nonzero dts %"PRId64", while the moov "
4993  "already has been written. Set the delay_moov flag to handle "
4994  "this case.\n",
4995  pkt->stream_index, pkt->dts);
4996  }
4997  trk->track_duration = pkt->dts - trk->start_dts + pkt->duration;
4998  trk->last_sample_is_subtitle_end = 0;
4999 
5000  if (pkt->pts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
5001  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING, "pts has no value\n");
5002  pkt->pts = pkt->dts;
5003  }
5004  if (pkt->dts != pkt->pts)
5005  trk->flags |= MOV_TRACK_CTTS;
5006  trk->cluster[trk->entry].cts = pkt->pts - pkt->dts;
5007  trk->cluster[trk->entry].flags = 0;
5008  if (trk->start_cts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
5009  trk->start_cts = pkt->pts - pkt->dts;
5010  if (trk->end_pts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
5011  trk->end_pts = trk->cluster[trk->entry].dts +
5012  trk->cluster[trk->entry].cts + pkt->duration;
5013  else
5014  trk->end_pts = FFMAX(trk->end_pts, trk->cluster[trk->entry].dts +
5015  trk->cluster[trk->entry].cts +
5016  pkt->duration);
5017 
5018  if (par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_VC1) {
5019  mov_parse_vc1_frame(pkt, trk);
5020  } else if (pkt->flags & AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY) {
5021  if (mov->mode == MODE_MOV && par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_MPEG2VIDEO &&
5022  trk->entry > 0) { // force sync sample for the first key frame
5023  mov_parse_mpeg2_frame(pkt, &trk->cluster[trk->entry].flags);
5024  if (trk->cluster[trk->entry].flags & MOV_PARTIAL_SYNC_SAMPLE)
5025  trk->flags |= MOV_TRACK_STPS;
5026  } else {
5027  trk->cluster[trk->entry].flags = MOV_SYNC_SAMPLE;
5028  }
5029  if (trk->cluster[trk->entry].flags & MOV_SYNC_SAMPLE)
5030  trk->has_keyframes++;
5031  }
5032  trk->entry++;
5033  trk->sample_count += samples_in_chunk;
5034  mov->mdat_size += size;
5035 
5036  if (trk->hint_track >= 0 && trk->hint_track < mov->nb_streams)
5037  ff_mov_add_hinted_packet(s, pkt, trk->hint_track, trk->entry,
5038  reformatted_data, size);
5039 
5040 end:
5041 err:
5042 
5043  av_free(reformatted_data);
5044  return ret;
5045 }
5046 
5047 static int mov_write_single_packet(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt)
5048 {
5049  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
5050  MOVTrack *trk = &mov->tracks[pkt->stream_index];
5051  AVCodecParameters *par = trk->par;
5052  int64_t frag_duration = 0;
5053  int size = pkt->size;
5054 
5055  int ret = check_pkt(s, pkt);
5056  if (ret < 0)
5057  return ret;
5058 
5059  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAG_DISCONT) {
5060  int i;
5061  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++)
5062  mov->tracks[i].frag_discont = 1;
5063  mov->flags &= ~FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAG_DISCONT;
5064  }
5065 
5066  if (!pkt->size) {
5067  if (trk->start_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE && trk->frag_discont) {
5068  trk->start_dts = pkt->dts;
5069  if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
5070  trk->start_cts = pkt->pts - pkt->dts;
5071  else
5072  trk->start_cts = 0;
5073  }
5074 
5075  if (trk->par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_MP4ALS ||
5076  trk->par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_FLAC) {
5077  int side_size = 0;
5078  uint8_t *side = av_packet_get_side_data(pkt, AV_PKT_DATA_NEW_EXTRADATA, &side_size);
5079  if (side && side_size > 0 && (side_size != par->extradata_size || memcmp(side, par->extradata, side_size))) {
5080  void *newextra = av_mallocz(side_size + AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE);
5081  if (!newextra)
5082  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5083  av_free(par->extradata);
5084  par->extradata = newextra;
5085  memcpy(par->extradata, side, side_size);
5086  par->extradata_size = side_size;
5087  mov->need_rewrite_extradata = 1;
5088  }
5089  }
5090 
5091  return 0; /* Discard 0 sized packets */
5092  }
5093 
5094  if (trk->entry && pkt->stream_index < s->nb_streams)
5095  frag_duration = av_rescale_q(pkt->dts - trk->cluster[0].dts,
5096  s->streams[pkt->stream_index]->time_base,
5097  AV_TIME_BASE_Q);
5098  if ((mov->max_fragment_duration &&
5099  frag_duration >= mov->max_fragment_duration) ||
5100  (mov->max_fragment_size && mov->mdat_size + size >= mov->max_fragment_size) ||
5101  (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAG_KEYFRAME &&
5102  par->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO &&
5103  trk->entry && pkt->flags & AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY)) {
5104  if (frag_duration >= mov->min_fragment_duration) {
5105  // Set the duration of this track to line up with the next
5106  // sample in this track. This avoids relying on AVPacket
5107  // duration, but only helps for this particular track, not
5108  // for the other ones that are flushed at the same time.
5109  trk->track_duration = pkt->dts - trk->start_dts;
5110  if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
5111  trk->end_pts = pkt->pts;
5112  else
5113  trk->end_pts = pkt->dts;
5114  trk->end_reliable = 1;
5115  mov_auto_flush_fragment(s, 0);
5116  }
5117  }
5118 
5119  return ff_mov_write_packet(s, pkt);
5120 }
5121 
5122 static int mov_write_subtitle_end_packet(AVFormatContext *s,
5123  int stream_index,
5124  int64_t dts) {
5125  AVPacket end;
5126  uint8_t data[2] = {0};
5127  int ret;
5128 
5129  av_init_packet(&end);
5130  end.size = sizeof(data);
5131  end.data = data;
5132  end.pts = dts;
5133  end.dts = dts;
5134  end.duration = 0;
5135  end.stream_index = stream_index;
5136 
5137  ret = mov_write_single_packet(s, &end);
5138  av_packet_unref(&end);
5139 
5140  return ret;
5141 }
5142 
5143 static int mov_write_packet(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt)
5144 {
5145  if (!pkt) {
5146  mov_flush_fragment(s, 1);
5147  return 1;
5148  } else {
5149  int i;
5150  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
5151  MOVTrack *trk = &mov->tracks[pkt->stream_index];
5152 
5153  if (!pkt->size)
5154  return mov_write_single_packet(s, pkt); /* Passthrough. */
5155 
5156  /*
5157  * Subtitles require special handling.
5158  *
5159  * 1) For full complaince, every track must have a sample at
5160  * dts == 0, which is rarely true for subtitles. So, as soon
5161  * as we see any packet with dts > 0, write an empty subtitle
5162  * at dts == 0 for any subtitle track with no samples in it.
5163  *
5164  * 2) For each subtitle track, check if the current packet's
5165  * dts is past the duration of the last subtitle sample. If
5166  * so, we now need to write an end sample for that subtitle.
5167  *
5168  * This must be done conditionally to allow for subtitles that
5169  * immediately replace each other, in which case an end sample
5170  * is not needed, and is, in fact, actively harmful.
5171  *
5172  * 3) See mov_write_trailer for how the final end sample is
5173  * handled.
5174  */
5175  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
5176  MOVTrack *trk = &mov->tracks[i];
5177  int ret;
5178 
5179  if (trk->par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_MOV_TEXT &&
5180  trk->track_duration < pkt->dts &&
5181  (trk->entry == 0 || !trk->last_sample_is_subtitle_end)) {
5182  ret = mov_write_subtitle_end_packet(s, i, trk->track_duration);
5183  if (ret < 0) return ret;
5184  trk->last_sample_is_subtitle_end = 1;
5185  }
5186  }
5187 
5188  if (trk->mode == MODE_MOV && trk->par->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
5189  AVPacket *opkt = pkt;
5190  int reshuffle_ret, ret;
5191  if (trk->is_unaligned_qt_rgb) {
5192  int64_t bpc = trk->par->bits_per_coded_sample != 15 ? trk->par->bits_per_coded_sample : 16;
5193  int expected_stride = ((trk->par->width * bpc + 15) >> 4)*2;
5194  reshuffle_ret = ff_reshuffle_raw_rgb(s, &pkt, trk->par, expected_stride);
5195  if (reshuffle_ret < 0)
5196  return reshuffle_ret;
5197  } else
5198  reshuffle_ret = 0;
5199  if (trk->par->format == AV_PIX_FMT_PAL8 && !trk->pal_done) {
5200  ret = ff_get_packet_palette(s, opkt, reshuffle_ret, trk->palette);
5201  if (ret < 0)
5202  goto fail;
5203  if (ret)
5204  trk->pal_done++;
5205  } else if (trk->par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_RAWVIDEO &&
5206  (trk->par->format == AV_PIX_FMT_GRAY8 ||
5207  trk->par->format == AV_PIX_FMT_MONOBLACK)) {
5208  for (i = 0; i < pkt->size; i++)
5209  pkt->data[i] = ~pkt->data[i];
5210  }
5211  if (reshuffle_ret) {
5212  ret = mov_write_single_packet(s, pkt);
5213 fail:
5214  if (reshuffle_ret)
5215  av_packet_free(&pkt);
5216  return ret;
5217  }
5218  }
5219 
5220  return mov_write_single_packet(s, pkt);
5221  }
5222 }
5223 
5224 // QuickTime chapters involve an additional text track with the chapter names
5225 // as samples, and a tref pointing from the other tracks to the chapter one.
5226 static int mov_create_chapter_track(AVFormatContext *s, int tracknum)
5227 {
5228  AVIOContext *pb;
5229 
5230  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
5231  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[tracknum];
5232  AVPacket pkt = { .stream_index = tracknum, .flags = AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY };
5233  int i, len;
5234 
5235  track->mode = mov->mode;
5236  track->tag = MKTAG('t','e','x','t');
5237  track->timescale = MOV_TIMESCALE;
5238  track->par = avcodec_parameters_alloc();
5239  if (!track->par)
5240  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5241  track->par->codec_type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE;
5242 #if 0
5243  // These properties are required to make QT recognize the chapter track
5244  uint8_t chapter_properties[43] = { 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, };
5245  if (ff_alloc_extradata(track->par, sizeof(chapter_properties)))
5246  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5247  memcpy(track->par->extradata, chapter_properties, sizeof(chapter_properties));
5248 #else
5249  if (avio_open_dyn_buf(&pb) >= 0) {
5250  int size;
5251  uint8_t *buf;
5252 
5253  /* Stub header (usually for Quicktime chapter track) */
5254  // TextSampleEntry
5255  avio_wb32(pb, 0x01); // displayFlags
5256  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // horizontal justification
5257  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // vertical justification
5258  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // bgColourRed
5259  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // bgColourGreen
5260  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // bgColourBlue
5261  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // bgColourAlpha
5262  // BoxRecord
5263  avio_wb16(pb, 0x00); // defTextBoxTop
5264  avio_wb16(pb, 0x00); // defTextBoxLeft
5265  avio_wb16(pb, 0x00); // defTextBoxBottom
5266  avio_wb16(pb, 0x00); // defTextBoxRight
5267  // StyleRecord
5268  avio_wb16(pb, 0x00); // startChar
5269  avio_wb16(pb, 0x00); // endChar
5270  avio_wb16(pb, 0x01); // fontID
5271  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // fontStyleFlags
5272  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // fontSize
5273  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // fgColourRed
5274  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // fgColourGreen
5275  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // fgColourBlue
5276  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // fgColourAlpha
5277  // FontTableBox
5278  avio_wb32(pb, 0x0D); // box size
5279  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "ftab"); // box atom name
5280  avio_wb16(pb, 0x01); // entry count
5281  // FontRecord
5282  avio_wb16(pb, 0x01); // font ID
5283  avio_w8(pb, 0x00); // font name length
5284 
5285  if ((size = avio_close_dyn_buf(pb, &buf)) > 0) {
5286  track->par->extradata = buf;
5287  track->par->extradata_size = size;
5288  } else {
5289  av_freep(&buf);
5290  }
5291  }
5292 #endif
5293 
5294  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_chapters; i++) {
5295  AVChapter *c = s->chapters[i];
5296  AVDictionaryEntry *t;
5297 
5298  int64_t end = av_rescale_q(c->end, c->time_base, (AVRational){1,MOV_TIMESCALE});
5299  pkt.pts = pkt.dts = av_rescale_q(c->start, c->time_base, (AVRational){1,MOV_TIMESCALE});
5300  pkt.duration = end - pkt.dts;
5301 
5302  if ((t = av_dict_get(c->metadata, "title", NULL, 0))) {
5303  static const char encd[12] = {
5304  0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x0C,
5305  'e', 'n', 'c', 'd',
5306  0x00, 0x00, 0x01, 0x00 };
5307  len = strlen(t->value);
5308  pkt.size = len + 2 + 12;
5309  pkt.data = av_malloc(pkt.size);
5310  if (!pkt.data)
5311  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5312  AV_WB16(pkt.data, len);
5313  memcpy(pkt.data + 2, t->value, len);
5314  memcpy(pkt.data + len + 2, encd, sizeof(encd));
5315  ff_mov_write_packet(s, &pkt);
5316  av_freep(&pkt.data);
5317  }
5318  }
5319 
5320  return 0;
5321 }

5333 static int mov_create_timecode_track(AVFormatContext *s, int index, int src_index, AVTimecode tc)
5334 {
5335  int ret;
5336  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
5337  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[index];
5338  AVStream *src_st = s->streams[src_index];
5339  AVPacket pkt = {.stream_index = index, .flags = AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY, .size = 4};
5340  AVRational rate = find_fps(s, src_st);
5341 
5342  /* tmcd track based on video stream */
5343  track->mode = mov->mode;
5344  track->tag = MKTAG('t','m','c','d');
5345  track->src_track = src_index;
5346  track->timescale = mov->tracks[src_index].timescale;
5347  if (tc.flags & AV_TIMECODE_FLAG_DROPFRAME)
5348  track->timecode_flags |= MOV_TIMECODE_FLAG_DROPFRAME;
5349 
5350  /* set st to src_st for metadata access*/
5351  track->st = src_st;
5352 
5353  /* encode context: tmcd data stream */
5354  track->par = avcodec_parameters_alloc();
5355  if (!track->par)
5356  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5357  track->par->codec_type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA;
5358  track->par->codec_tag = track->tag;
5359  track->st->avg_frame_rate = av_inv_q(rate);
5360 
5361  /* the tmcd track just contains one packet with the frame number */
5362  pkt.data = av_malloc(pkt.size);
5363  if (!pkt.data)
5364  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5365  AV_WB32(pkt.data, tc.start);
5366  ret = ff_mov_write_packet(s, &pkt);
5367  av_free(pkt.data);
5368  return ret;
5369 }
5370 
5371 /*
5372  * st->disposition controls the "enabled" flag in the tkhd tag.
5373  * QuickTime will not play a track if it is not enabled. So make sure
5374  * that one track of each type (audio, video, subtitle) is enabled.
5375  *
5376  * Subtitles are special. For audio and video, setting "enabled" also
5377  * makes the track "default" (i.e. it is rendered when played). For
5378  * subtitles, an "enabled" subtitle is not rendered by default, but
5379  * if no subtitle is enabled, the subtitle menu in QuickTime will be
5380  * empty!
5381  */
5382 static void enable_tracks(AVFormatContext *s)
5383 {
5384  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
5385  int i;
5386  int enabled[AVMEDIA_TYPE_NB];
5387  int first[AVMEDIA_TYPE_NB];
5388 
5389  for (i = 0; i < AVMEDIA_TYPE_NB; i++) {
5390  enabled[i] = 0;
5391  first[i] = -1;
5392  }
5393 
5394  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
5395  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
5396 
5397  if (st->codecpar->codec_type <= AVMEDIA_TYPE_UNKNOWN ||
5398  st->codecpar->codec_type >= AVMEDIA_TYPE_NB)
5399  continue;
5400 
5401  if (first[st->codecpar->codec_type] < 0)
5402  first[st->codecpar->codec_type] = i;
5403  if (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_DEFAULT) {
5404  mov->tracks[i].flags |= MOV_TRACK_ENABLED;
5405  enabled[st->codecpar->codec_type]++;
5406  }
5407  }
5408 
5409  for (i = 0; i < AVMEDIA_TYPE_NB; i++) {
5410  switch (i) {
5411  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
5412  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
5413  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE:
5414  if (enabled[i] > 1)
5415  mov->per_stream_grouping = 1;
5416  if (!enabled[i] && first[i] >= 0)
5417  mov->tracks[first[i]].flags |= MOV_TRACK_ENABLED;
5418  break;
5419  }
5420  }
5421 }
5422 
5423 static void mov_free(AVFormatContext *s)
5424 {
5425  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
5426  int i;
5427 
5428  if (mov->chapter_track) {
5429  if (mov->tracks[mov->chapter_track].par)
5430  av_freep(&mov->tracks[mov->chapter_track].par->extradata);
5431  av_freep(&mov->tracks[mov->chapter_track].par);
5432  }
5433 
5434  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
5435  if (mov->tracks[i].tag == MKTAG('r','t','p',' '))
5436  ff_mov_close_hinting(&mov->tracks[i]);
5437  else if (mov->tracks[i].tag == MKTAG('t','m','c','d') && mov->nb_meta_tmcd)
5438  av_freep(&mov->tracks[i].par);
5439  av_freep(&mov->tracks[i].cluster);
5440  av_freep(&mov->tracks[i].frag_info);
5441 
5442  if (mov->tracks[i].vos_len)
5443  av_freep(&mov->tracks[i].vos_data);
5444 
5445  ff_mov_cenc_free(&mov->tracks[i].cenc);
5446  }
5447 
5448  av_freep(&mov->tracks);
5449 }
