5451 static uint32_t rgb_to_yuv(uint32_t rgb)
5452 {
5453  uint8_t r, g, b;
5454  int y, cb, cr;
5455 
5456  r = (rgb >> 16) & 0xFF;
5457  g = (rgb >> 8) & 0xFF;
5458  b = (rgb ) & 0xFF;
5459 
5460  y = av_clip_uint8(( 16000 + 257 * r + 504 * g + 98 * b)/1000);
5461  cb = av_clip_uint8((128000 - 148 * r - 291 * g + 439 * b)/1000);
5462  cr = av_clip_uint8((128000 + 439 * r - 368 * g - 71 * b)/1000);
5463 
5464  return (y << 16) | (cr << 8) | cb;
5465 }
5466 
5467 static int mov_create_dvd_sub_decoder_specific_info(MOVTrack *track,
5468  AVStream *st)
5469 {
5470  int i, width = 720, height = 480;
5471  int have_palette = 0, have_size = 0;
5472  uint32_t palette[16];
5473  char *cur = st->codecpar->extradata;
5474 
5475  while (cur && *cur) {
5476  if (strncmp("palette:", cur, 8) == 0) {
5477  int i, count;
5478  count = sscanf(cur + 8,
5479  "%06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", "
5480  "%06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", "
5481  "%06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", "
5482  "%06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32", %06"PRIx32"",
5483  &palette[ 0], &palette[ 1], &palette[ 2], &palette[ 3],
5484  &palette[ 4], &palette[ 5], &palette[ 6], &palette[ 7],
5485  &palette[ 8], &palette[ 9], &palette[10], &palette[11],
5486  &palette[12], &palette[13], &palette[14], &palette[15]);
5487 
5488  for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
5489  palette[i] = rgb_to_yuv(palette[i]);
5490  }
5491  have_palette = 1;
5492  } else if (!strncmp("size:", cur, 5)) {
5493  sscanf(cur + 5, "%dx%d", &width, &height);
5494  have_size = 1;
5495  }
5496  if (have_palette && have_size)
5497  break;
5498  cur += strcspn(cur, "\n\r");
5499  cur += strspn(cur, "\n\r");
5500  }
5501  if (have_palette) {
5502  track->vos_data = av_malloc(16*4);
5503  if (!track->vos_data)
5504  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5505  for (i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
5506  AV_WB32(track->vos_data + i * 4, palette[i]);
5507  }
5508  track->vos_len = 16 * 4;
5509  }
5510  st->codecpar->width = width;
5511  st->codecpar->height = track->height = height;
5512 
5513  return 0;
5514 }
5515 
5516 static int mov_init(AVFormatContext *s)
5517 {
5518  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
5519  AVDictionaryEntry *global_tcr = av_dict_get(s->metadata, "timecode", NULL, 0);
5520  int i, ret, hint_track = 0, tmcd_track = 0;
5521 
5522  mov->fc = s;
5523 
5524  /* Default mode == MP4 */
5525  mov->mode = MODE_MP4;
5526 
5527  if (s->oformat) {
5528  if (!strcmp("3gp", s->oformat->name)) mov->mode = MODE_3GP;
5529  else if (!strcmp("3g2", s->oformat->name)) mov->mode = MODE_3GP|MODE_3G2;
5530  else if (!strcmp("mov", s->oformat->name)) mov->mode = MODE_MOV;
5531  else if (!strcmp("psp", s->oformat->name)) mov->mode = MODE_PSP;
5532  else if (!strcmp("ipod",s->oformat->name)) mov->mode = MODE_IPOD;
5533  else if (!strcmp("ismv",s->oformat->name)) mov->mode = MODE_ISM;
5534  else if (!strcmp("f4v", s->oformat->name)) mov->mode = MODE_F4V;
5535  }
5536 
5537  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DELAY_MOOV)
5538  mov->flags |= FF_MOV_FLAG_EMPTY_MOOV;
5539 
5540  /* Set the FRAGMENT flag if any of the fragmentation methods are
5541  * enabled. */
5542  if (mov->max_fragment_duration || mov->max_fragment_size ||
5543  mov->flags & (FF_MOV_FLAG_EMPTY_MOOV |
5544  FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAG_KEYFRAME |
5545  FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAG_CUSTOM))
5546  mov->flags |= FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT;
5547 
5548  /* Set other implicit flags immediately */
5549  if (mov->mode == MODE_ISM)
5550  mov->flags |= FF_MOV_FLAG_EMPTY_MOOV | FF_MOV_FLAG_SEPARATE_MOOF |
5551  FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT;
5552  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DASH)
5553  mov->flags |= FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT | FF_MOV_FLAG_EMPTY_MOOV |
5554  FF_MOV_FLAG_DEFAULT_BASE_MOOF;
5555 
5556  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_EMPTY_MOOV && s->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_AUTO_BSF) {
5557  av_log(s, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "Empty MOOV enabled; disabling automatic bitstream filtering\n");
5558  s->flags &= ~AVFMT_FLAG_AUTO_BSF;
5559  }
5560 
5561  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FASTSTART) {
5562  mov->reserved_moov_size = -1;
5563  }
5564 
5565  if (mov->use_editlist < 0) {
5566  mov->use_editlist = 1;
5567  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT &&
5568  !(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DELAY_MOOV)) {
5569  // If we can avoid needing an edit list by shifting the
5570  // tracks, prefer that over (trying to) write edit lists
5571  // in fragmented output.
5572  if (s->avoid_negative_ts == AVFMT_AVOID_NEG_TS_AUTO ||
5573  s->avoid_negative_ts == AVFMT_AVOID_NEG_TS_MAKE_ZERO)
5574  mov->use_editlist = 0;
5575  }
5576  }
5577  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_EMPTY_MOOV &&
5578  !(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DELAY_MOOV) && mov->use_editlist)
5579  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING, "No meaningful edit list will be written when using empty_moov without delay_moov\n");
5580 
5581  if (!mov->use_editlist && s->avoid_negative_ts == AVFMT_AVOID_NEG_TS_AUTO)
5582  s->avoid_negative_ts = AVFMT_AVOID_NEG_TS_MAKE_ZERO;
5583 
5584  /* Clear the omit_tfhd_offset flag if default_base_moof is set;
5585  * if the latter is set that's enough and omit_tfhd_offset doesn't
5586  * add anything extra on top of that. */
5587  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_OMIT_TFHD_OFFSET &&
5588  mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DEFAULT_BASE_MOOF)
5589  mov->flags &= ~FF_MOV_FLAG_OMIT_TFHD_OFFSET;
5590 
5591  if (mov->frag_interleave &&
5592  mov->flags & (FF_MOV_FLAG_OMIT_TFHD_OFFSET | FF_MOV_FLAG_SEPARATE_MOOF)) {
5593  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR,
5594  "Sample interleaving in fragments is mutually exclusive with "
5595  "omit_tfhd_offset and separate_moof\n");
5596  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5597  }
5598 
5599  /* Non-seekable output is ok if using fragmentation. If ism_lookahead
5600  * is enabled, we don't support non-seekable output at all. */
5601  if (!s->pb->seekable &&
5602  (!(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT) || mov->ism_lookahead)) {
5603  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "muxer does not support non seekable output\n");
5604  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5605  }
5606 
5607  mov->nb_streams = s->nb_streams;
5608  if (mov->mode & (MODE_MP4|MODE_MOV|MODE_IPOD) && s->nb_chapters)
5609  mov->chapter_track = mov->nb_streams++;
5610 
5611  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_RTP_HINT) {
5612  /* Add hint tracks for each audio and video stream */
5613  hint_track = mov->nb_streams;
5614  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
5615  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
5616  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ||
5617  st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
5618  mov->nb_streams++;
5619  }
5620  }
5621  }
5622 
5623  if ( mov->write_tmcd == -1 && (mov->mode == MODE_MOV || mov->mode == MODE_MP4)
5624  || mov->write_tmcd == 1) {
5625  tmcd_track = mov->nb_streams;
5626 
5627  /* +1 tmcd track for each video stream with a timecode */
5628  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
5629  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
5630  AVDictionaryEntry *t = global_tcr;
5631  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO &&
5632  (t || (t=av_dict_get(st->metadata, "timecode", NULL, 0)))) {
5633  AVTimecode tc;
5634  ret = mov_check_timecode_track(s, &tc, i, t->value);
5635  if (ret >= 0)
5636  mov->nb_meta_tmcd++;
5637  }
5638  }
5639 
5640  /* check if there is already a tmcd track to remux */
5641  if (mov->nb_meta_tmcd) {
5642  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
5643  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
5644  if (st->codecpar->codec_tag == MKTAG('t','m','c','d')) {
5645  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING, "You requested a copy of the original timecode track "
5646  "so timecode metadata are now ignored\n");
5647  mov->nb_meta_tmcd = 0;
5648  }
5649  }
5650  }
5651 
5652  mov->nb_streams += mov->nb_meta_tmcd;
5653  }
5654 
5655  // Reserve an extra stream for chapters for the case where chapters
5656  // are written in the trailer
5657  mov->tracks = av_mallocz_array((mov->nb_streams + 1), sizeof(*mov->tracks));
5658  if (!mov->tracks)
5659  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5660 
5661  if (mov->encryption_scheme_str != NULL && strcmp(mov->encryption_scheme_str, "none") != 0) {
5662  if (strcmp(mov->encryption_scheme_str, "cenc-aes-ctr") == 0) {
5663  mov->encryption_scheme = MOV_ENC_CENC_AES_CTR;
5664 
5665  if (mov->encryption_key_len != AES_CTR_KEY_SIZE) {
5666  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid encryption key len %d expected %d\n",
5667  mov->encryption_key_len, AES_CTR_KEY_SIZE);
5668  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5669  }
5670 
5671  if (mov->encryption_kid_len != CENC_KID_SIZE) {
5672  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid encryption kid len %d expected %d\n",
5673  mov->encryption_kid_len, CENC_KID_SIZE);
5674  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5675  }
5676  } else {
5677  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "unsupported encryption scheme %s\n",
5678  mov->encryption_scheme_str);
5679  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5680  }
5681  }
5682 
5683  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
5684  AVStream *st= s->streams[i];
5685  MOVTrack *track= &mov->tracks[i];
5686  AVDictionaryEntry *lang = av_dict_get(st->metadata, "language", NULL,0);
5687 
5688  track->st = st;
5689  track->par = st->codecpar;
5690  track->language = ff_mov_iso639_to_lang(lang?lang->value:"und", mov->mode!=MODE_MOV);
5691  if (track->language < 0)
5692  track->language = 0;
5693  track->mode = mov->mode;
5694  track->tag = mov_find_codec_tag(s, track);
5695  if (!track->tag) {
5696  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Could not find tag for codec %s in stream #%d, "
5697  "codec not currently supported in container\n",
5698  avcodec_get_name(st->codecpar->codec_id), i);
5699  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5700  }
5701  /* If hinting of this track is enabled by a later hint track,
5702  * this is updated. */
5703  track->hint_track = -1;
5704  track->start_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
5705  track->start_cts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
5706  track->end_pts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
5707  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
5708  if (track->tag == MKTAG('m','x','3','p') || track->tag == MKTAG('m','x','3','n') ||
5709  track->tag == MKTAG('m','x','4','p') || track->tag == MKTAG('m','x','4','n') ||
5710  track->tag == MKTAG('m','x','5','p') || track->tag == MKTAG('m','x','5','n')) {
5711  if (st->codecpar->width != 720 || (st->codecpar->height != 608 && st->codecpar->height != 512)) {
5712  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "D-10/IMX must use 720x608 or 720x512 video resolution\n");
5713  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5714  }
5715  track->height = track->tag >> 24 == 'n' ? 486 : 576;
5716  }
5717  if (mov->video_track_timescale) {
5718  track->timescale = mov->video_track_timescale;
5719  } else {
5720  track->timescale = st->time_base.den;
5721  while(track->timescale < 10000)
5722  track->timescale *= 2;
5723  }
5724  if (st->codecpar->width > 65535 || st->codecpar->height > 65535) {
5725  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Resolution %dx%d too large for mov/mp4\n", st->codecpar->width, st->codecpar->height);
5726  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5727  }
5728  if (track->mode == MODE_MOV && track->timescale > 100000)
5729  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING,
5730  "WARNING codec timebase is very high. If duration is too long,\n"
5731  "file may not be playable by quicktime. Specify a shorter timebase\n"
5732  "or choose different container.\n");
5733  if (track->mode == MODE_MOV &&
5734  track->par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_RAWVIDEO &&
5735  track->tag == MKTAG('r','a','w',' ')) {
5736  enum AVPixelFormat pix_fmt = track->par->format;
5737  if (pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE && track->par->bits_per_coded_sample == 1)
5738  pix_fmt = AV_PIX_FMT_MONOWHITE;
5739  track->is_unaligned_qt_rgb =
5740  pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_RGB24 ||
5741  pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_BGR24 ||
5742  pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_PAL8 ||
5743  pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_GRAY8 ||
5744  pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_MONOWHITE ||
5745  pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_MONOBLACK;
5746  }
5747  if (track->par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_VP9) {
5748  if (track->mode != MODE_MP4) {
5749  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "VP9 only supported in MP4.\n");
5750  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5751  }
5752  if (s->strict_std_compliance > FF_COMPLIANCE_EXPERIMENTAL) {
5753  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR,
5754  "VP9 in MP4 support is experimental, add "
5755  "'-strict %d' if you want to use it.\n",
5756  FF_COMPLIANCE_EXPERIMENTAL);
5757  return AVERROR_EXPERIMENTAL;
5758  }
5759  }
5760  } else if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
5761  track->timescale = st->codecpar->sample_rate;
5762  if (!st->codecpar->frame_size && !av_get_bits_per_sample(st->codecpar->codec_id)) {
5763  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING, "track %d: codec frame size is not set\n", i);
5764  track->audio_vbr = 1;
5765  }else if (st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_ADPCM_MS ||
5766  st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_ADPCM_IMA_WAV ||
5767  st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_ILBC){
5768  if (!st->codecpar->block_align) {
5769  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "track %d: codec block align is not set for adpcm\n", i);
5770  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5771  }
5772  track->sample_size = st->codecpar->block_align;
5773  }else if (st->codecpar->frame_size > 1){ /* assume compressed audio */
5774  track->audio_vbr = 1;
5775  }else{
5776  track->sample_size = (av_get_bits_per_sample(st->codecpar->codec_id) >> 3) * st->codecpar->channels;
5777  }
5778  if (st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_ILBC ||
5779  st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_ADPCM_IMA_QT) {
5780  track->audio_vbr = 1;
5781  }
5782  if (track->mode != MODE_MOV &&
5783  track->par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_MP3 && track->timescale < 16000) {
5784  if (s->strict_std_compliance >= FF_COMPLIANCE_NORMAL) {
5785  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "track %d: muxing mp3 at %dhz is not standard, to mux anyway set strict to -1\n",
5786  i, track->par->sample_rate);
5787  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5788  } else {
5789  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING, "track %d: muxing mp3 at %dhz is not standard in MP4\n",
5790  i, track->par->sample_rate);
5791  }
5792  }
5793  if (track->par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_FLAC) {
5794  if (track->mode != MODE_MP4) {
5795  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "FLAC only supported in MP4.\n");
5796  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5797  }
5798  if (s->strict_std_compliance > FF_COMPLIANCE_EXPERIMENTAL) {
5799  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR,
5800  "FLAC in MP4 support is experimental, add "
5801  "'-strict %d' if you want to use it.\n",
5802  FF_COMPLIANCE_EXPERIMENTAL);
5803  return AVERROR_EXPERIMENTAL;
5804  }
5805  }
5806  } else if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE) {
5807  track->timescale = st->time_base.den;
5808  } else if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA) {
5809  track->timescale = st->time_base.den;
5810  } else {
5811  track->timescale = MOV_TIMESCALE;
5812  }
5813  if (!track->height)
5814  track->height = st->codecpar->height;
5815  /* The ism specific timescale isn't mandatory, but is assumed by
5816  * some tools, such as mp4split. */
5817  if (mov->mode == MODE_ISM)
5818  track->timescale = 10000000;
5819 
5820  avpriv_set_pts_info(st, 64, 1, track->timescale);
5821 
5822  if (mov->encryption_scheme == MOV_ENC_CENC_AES_CTR) {
5823  ret = ff_mov_cenc_init(&track->cenc, mov->encryption_key,
5824  track->par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264, s->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_BITEXACT);
5825  if (ret)
5826  return ret;
5827  }
5828  }
5829 
5830  enable_tracks(s);
5831  return 0;
5832 }
5833 
5834 static int mov_write_header(AVFormatContext *s)
5835 {
5836  AVIOContext *pb = s->pb;
5837  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
5838  AVDictionaryEntry *t, *global_tcr = av_dict_get(s->metadata, "timecode", NULL, 0);
5839  int i, ret, hint_track = 0, tmcd_track = 0, nb_tracks = s->nb_streams;
5840 
5841  if (mov->mode & (MODE_MP4|MODE_MOV|MODE_IPOD) && s->nb_chapters)
5842  nb_tracks++;
5843 
5844  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_RTP_HINT) {
5845  /* Add hint tracks for each audio and video stream */
5846  hint_track = nb_tracks;
5847  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
5848  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
5849  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ||
5850  st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
5851  nb_tracks++;
5852  }
5853  }
5854  }
5855 
5856  if (mov->mode == MODE_MOV || mov->mode == MODE_MP4)
5857  tmcd_track = nb_tracks;
5858 
5859  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
5860  int j;
5861  AVStream *st= s->streams[i];
5862  MOVTrack *track= &mov->tracks[i];
5863 
5864  /* copy extradata if it exists */
5865  if (st->codecpar->extradata_size) {
5866  if (st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_DVD_SUBTITLE)
5867  mov_create_dvd_sub_decoder_specific_info(track, st);
5868  else if (!TAG_IS_AVCI(track->tag) && st->codecpar->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_DNXHD) {
5869  track->vos_len = st->codecpar->extradata_size;
5870  track->vos_data = av_malloc(track->vos_len);
5871  if (!track->vos_data) {
5872  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5873  }
5874  memcpy(track->vos_data, st->codecpar->extradata, track->vos_len);
5875  }
5876  }
5877 
5878  if (st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
5879  track->par->channel_layout != AV_CH_LAYOUT_MONO)
5880  continue;
5881 
5882  for (j = 0; j < s->nb_streams; j++) {
5883  AVStream *stj= s->streams[j];
5884  MOVTrack *trackj= &mov->tracks[j];
5885  if (j == i)
5886  continue;
5887 
5888  if (stj->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
5889  trackj->par->channel_layout != AV_CH_LAYOUT_MONO ||
5890  trackj->language != track->language ||
5891  trackj->tag != track->tag
5892  )
5893  continue;
5894  track->multichannel_as_mono++;
5895  }
5896  }
5897 
5898  if (!(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DELAY_MOOV)) {
5899  if ((ret = mov_write_identification(pb, s)) < 0)
5900  return ret;
5901  }
5902 
5903  if (mov->reserved_moov_size){
5904  mov->reserved_header_pos = avio_tell(pb);
5905  if (mov->reserved_moov_size > 0)
5906  avio_skip(pb, mov->reserved_moov_size);
5907  }
5908 
5909  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT) {
5910  /* If no fragmentation options have been set, set a default. */
5911  if (!(mov->flags & (FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAG_KEYFRAME |
5912  FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAG_CUSTOM)) &&
5913  !mov->max_fragment_duration && !mov->max_fragment_size)
5914  mov->flags |= FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAG_KEYFRAME;
5915  } else {
5916  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FASTSTART)
5917  mov->reserved_header_pos = avio_tell(pb);
5918  mov_write_mdat_tag(pb, mov);
5919  }
5920 
5921  ff_parse_creation_time_metadata(s, &mov->time, 1);
5922  if (mov->time)
5923  mov->time += 0x7C25B080; // 1970 based -> 1904 based
5924 
5925  if (mov->chapter_track)
5926  if ((ret = mov_create_chapter_track(s, mov->chapter_track)) < 0)
5927  return ret;
5928 
5929  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_RTP_HINT) {
5930  /* Initialize the hint tracks for each audio and video stream */
5931  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
5932  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
5933  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ||
5934  st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
5935  if ((ret = ff_mov_init_hinting(s, hint_track, i)) < 0)
5936  return ret;
5937  hint_track++;
5938  }
5939  }
5940  }
5941 
5942  if (mov->nb_meta_tmcd) {
5943  /* Initialize the tmcd tracks */
5944  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
5945  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
5946  t = global_tcr;
5947 
5948  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
5949  AVTimecode tc;
5950  if (!t)
5951  t = av_dict_get(st->metadata, "timecode", NULL, 0);
5952  if (!t)
5953  continue;
5954  if (mov_check_timecode_track(s, &tc, i, t->value) < 0)
5955  continue;
5956  if ((ret = mov_create_timecode_track(s, tmcd_track, i, tc)) < 0)
5957  return ret;
5958  tmcd_track++;
5959  }
5960  }
5961  }
5962 
5963  avio_flush(pb);
5964 
5965  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_ISML)
5966  mov_write_isml_manifest(pb, mov, s);
5967 
5968  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_EMPTY_MOOV &&
5969  !(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_DELAY_MOOV)) {
5970  if ((ret = mov_write_moov_tag(pb, mov, s)) < 0)
5971  return ret;
5972  avio_flush(pb);
5973  mov->moov_written = 1;
5974  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_GLOBAL_SIDX)
5975  mov->reserved_header_pos = avio_tell(pb);
5976  }
5977 
5978  return 0;
5979 }
5980 
5981 static int get_moov_size(AVFormatContext *s)
5982 {
5983  int ret;
5984  AVIOContext *moov_buf;
5985  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
5986 
5987  if ((ret = ffio_open_null_buf(&moov_buf)) < 0)
5988  return ret;
5989  if ((ret = mov_write_moov_tag(moov_buf, mov, s)) < 0)
5990  return ret;
5991  return ffio_close_null_buf(moov_buf);
5992 }
5993 
5994 static int get_sidx_size(AVFormatContext *s)
5995 {
5996  int ret;
5997  AVIOContext *buf;
5998  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
5999 
6000  if ((ret = ffio_open_null_buf(&buf)) < 0)
6001  return ret;
6002  mov_write_sidx_tags(buf, mov, -1, 0);
6003  return ffio_close_null_buf(buf);
6004 }
6005 
6006 /*
6007  * This function gets the moov size if moved to the top of the file: the chunk
6008  * offset table can switch between stco (32-bit entries) to co64 (64-bit
6009  * entries) when the moov is moved to the beginning, so the size of the moov
6010  * would change. It also updates the chunk offset tables.
6011  */
6012 static int compute_moov_size(AVFormatContext *s)
6013 {
6014  int i, moov_size, moov_size2;
6015  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
6016 
6017  moov_size = get_moov_size(s);
6018  if (moov_size < 0)
6019  return moov_size;
6020 
6021  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++)
6022  mov->tracks[i].data_offset += moov_size;
6023 
6024  moov_size2 = get_moov_size(s);
6025  if (moov_size2 < 0)
6026  return moov_size2;
6027 
6028  /* if the size changed, we just switched from stco to co64 and need to
6029  * update the offsets */
6030  if (moov_size2 != moov_size)
6031  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++)
6032  mov->tracks[i].data_offset += moov_size2 - moov_size;
6033 
6034  return moov_size2;
6035 }
6036 
6037 static int compute_sidx_size(AVFormatContext *s)
6038 {
6039  int i, sidx_size;
6040  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
6041 
6042  sidx_size = get_sidx_size(s);
6043  if (sidx_size < 0)
6044  return sidx_size;
6045 
6046  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++)
6047  mov->tracks[i].data_offset += sidx_size;
6048 
6049  return sidx_size;
6050 }
6051 
6052 static int shift_data(AVFormatContext *s)
6053 {
6054  int ret = 0, moov_size;
6055  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
6056  int64_t pos, pos_end = avio_tell(s->pb);
6057  uint8_t *buf, *read_buf[2];
6058  int read_buf_id = 0;
6059  int read_size[2];
6060  AVIOContext *read_pb;
6061 
6062  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT)
6063  moov_size = compute_sidx_size(s);
6064  else
6065  moov_size = compute_moov_size(s);
6066  if (moov_size < 0)
6067  return moov_size;
6068 
6069  buf = av_malloc(moov_size * 2);
6070  if (!buf)
6071  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
6072  read_buf[0] = buf;
6073  read_buf[1] = buf + moov_size;
6074 
6075  /* Shift the data: the AVIO context of the output can only be used for
6076  * writing, so we re-open the same output, but for reading. It also avoids
6077  * a read/seek/write/seek back and forth. */
6078  avio_flush(s->pb);
6079  ret = s->io_open(s, &read_pb, s->filename, AVIO_FLAG_READ, NULL);
6080  if (ret < 0) {
6081  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Unable to re-open %s output file for "
6082  "the second pass (faststart)\n", s->filename);
6083  goto end;
6084  }
6085 
6086  /* mark the end of the shift to up to the last data we wrote, and get ready
6087  * for writing */
6088  pos_end = avio_tell(s->pb);
6089  avio_seek(s->pb, mov->reserved_header_pos + moov_size, SEEK_SET);
6090 
6091  /* start reading at where the new moov will be placed */
6092  avio_seek(read_pb, mov->reserved_header_pos, SEEK_SET);
6093  pos = avio_tell(read_pb);
6094 
6095 #define READ_BLOCK do { \
6096  read_size[read_buf_id] = avio_read(read_pb, read_buf[read_buf_id], moov_size); \
6097  read_buf_id ^= 1; \
6098 } while (0)
6099 
6100  /* shift data by chunk of at most moov_size */
6101  READ_BLOCK;
6102  do {
6103  int n;
6104  READ_BLOCK;
6105  n = read_size[read_buf_id];
6106  if (n <= 0)
6107  break;
6108  avio_write(s->pb, read_buf[read_buf_id], n);
6109  pos += n;
6110  } while (pos < pos_end);
6111  ff_format_io_close(s, &read_pb);
6112 
6113 end:
6114  av_free(buf);
6115  return ret;
6116 }
6117 
6118 static int mov_write_trailer(AVFormatContext *s)
6119 {
6120  MOVMuxContext *mov = s->priv_data;
6121  AVIOContext *pb = s->pb;
6122  int res = 0;
6123  int i;
6124  int64_t moov_pos;
6125 
6126  if (mov->need_rewrite_extradata) {
6127  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
6128  MOVTrack *track = &mov->tracks[i];
6129  AVCodecParameters *par = track->par;
6130 
6131  track->vos_len = par->extradata_size;
6132  track->vos_data = av_malloc(track->vos_len);
6133  if (!track->vos_data)
6134  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
6135  memcpy(track->vos_data, par->extradata, track->vos_len);
6136  }
6137  mov->need_rewrite_extradata = 0;
6138  }
6139 
6140  /*
6141  * Before actually writing the trailer, make sure that there are no
6142  * dangling subtitles, that need a terminating sample.
6143  */
6144  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++) {
6145  MOVTrack *trk = &mov->tracks[i];
6146  if (trk->par->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_MOV_TEXT &&
6147  !trk->last_sample_is_subtitle_end) {
6148  mov_write_subtitle_end_packet(s, i, trk->track_duration);
6149  trk->last_sample_is_subtitle_end = 1;
6150  }
6151  }
6152 
6153  // If there were no chapters when the header was written, but there
6154  // are chapters now, write them in the trailer. This only works
6155  // when we are not doing fragments.
6156  if (!mov->chapter_track && !(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT)) {
6157  if (mov->mode & (MODE_MP4|MODE_MOV|MODE_IPOD) && s->nb_chapters) {
6158  mov->chapter_track = mov->nb_streams++;
6159  if ((res = mov_create_chapter_track(s, mov->chapter_track)) < 0)
6160  return res;
6161  }
6162  }
6163 
6164  if (!(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FRAGMENT)) {
6165  moov_pos = avio_tell(pb);
6166 
6167  /* Write size of mdat tag */
6168  if (mov->mdat_size + 8 <= UINT32_MAX) {
6169  avio_seek(pb, mov->mdat_pos, SEEK_SET);
6170  avio_wb32(pb, mov->mdat_size + 8);
6171  } else {
6172  /* overwrite 'wide' placeholder atom */
6173  avio_seek(pb, mov->mdat_pos - 8, SEEK_SET);
6174  /* special value: real atom size will be 64 bit value after
6175  * tag field */
6176  avio_wb32(pb, 1);
6177  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "mdat");
6178  avio_wb64(pb, mov->mdat_size + 16);
6179  }
6180  avio_seek(pb, mov->reserved_moov_size > 0 ? mov->reserved_header_pos : moov_pos, SEEK_SET);
6181 
6182  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_FASTSTART) {
6183  av_log(s, AV_LOG_INFO, "Starting second pass: moving the moov atom to the beginning of the file\n");
6184  res = shift_data(s);
6185  if (res < 0)
6186  return res;
6187  avio_seek(pb, mov->reserved_header_pos, SEEK_SET);
6188  if ((res = mov_write_moov_tag(pb, mov, s)) < 0)
6189  return res;
6190  } else if (mov->reserved_moov_size > 0) {
6191  int64_t size;
6192  if ((res = mov_write_moov_tag(pb, mov, s)) < 0)
6193  return res;
6194  size = mov->reserved_moov_size - (avio_tell(pb) - mov->reserved_header_pos);
6195  if (size < 8){
6196  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "reserved_moov_size is too small, needed %"PRId64" additional\n", 8-size);
6197  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
6198  }
6199  avio_wb32(pb, size);
6200  ffio_wfourcc(pb, "free");
6201  ffio_fill(pb, 0, size - 8);
6202  avio_seek(pb, moov_pos, SEEK_SET);
6203  } else {
6204  if ((res = mov_write_moov_tag(pb, mov, s)) < 0)
6205  return res;
6206  }
6207  res = 0;
6208  } else {
6209  mov_auto_flush_fragment(s, 1);
6210  for (i = 0; i < mov->nb_streams; i++)
6211  mov->tracks[i].data_offset = 0;
6212  if (mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_GLOBAL_SIDX) {
6213  int64_t end;
6214  av_log(s, AV_LOG_INFO, "Starting second pass: inserting sidx atoms\n");
6215  res = shift_data(s);
6216  if (res < 0)
6217  return res;
6218  end = avio_tell(pb);
6219  avio_seek(pb, mov->reserved_header_pos, SEEK_SET);
6220  mov_write_sidx_tags(pb, mov, -1, 0);
6221  avio_seek(pb, end, SEEK_SET);
6222  avio_write_marker(s->pb, AV_NOPTS_VALUE, AVIO_DATA_MARKER_TRAILER);
6223  mov_write_mfra_tag(pb, mov);
6224  } else if (!(mov->flags & FF_MOV_FLAG_SKIP_TRAILER)) {
6225  avio_write_marker(s->pb, AV_NOPTS_VALUE, AVIO_DATA_MARKER_TRAILER);
6226  mov_write_mfra_tag(pb, mov);
6227  }
6228  }
6229 
6230  return res;
6231 }
6232 
6233 static int mov_check_bitstream(struct AVFormatContext *s, const AVPacket *pkt)
6234 {
6235  int ret = 1;
6236  AVStream *st = s->streams[pkt->stream_index];
6237 
6238  if (st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_AAC) {
6239  if (pkt->size > 2 && (AV_RB16(pkt->data) & 0xfff0) == 0xfff0)
6240  ret = ff_stream_add_bitstream_filter(st, "aac_adtstoasc", NULL);
6241  }
6242 
6243  return ret;
6244 }
